2⁵. dictator: an extraordinary magistrate appointed in time of peril. He held his office for six months only, and was preceded by twenty-four lictors with the fasces and axes. He had associated with him a lieutenant called the Master oi Horse (magister equitum), whom he usually appointed himself. As he had no colleague, and was irresponsible, his power was greater than that of the consul. impetum mori tregit: i.e. he checked Hannibal's victorious mreer by a policy oi delay.. , His design was to harass Hannibal and tire him out, without risking a decisive battle. From the successful outcome oi these tactics ‘F abian policy ³ has become proverbial.
